definition: to have nothing in common with each other (idiom)
each other/one another/mutually/fret on the neck of a pipa 琵琶[pi2 pa5] (a fret on the soundboard is called a 品[pin3])
appearance/portrait/picture/government minister/(physics) phase/(literary) to appraise (esp. by scrutinizing physical features)/to read sb's fortune (by physiognomy, palmistry etc)

sentences.english: Use of the Likert scale differed among instruments.
sentences.chinese: 在不同诊断工具间，对里克特等级的使用各不相同。

sentences.english: Since being residentially different, title is also each and not identical.
sentences.chinese: 由于居住地不同，称谓也各不相同。

sentences.english: PC companies have dabbled in retail with varying results.
sentences.chinese: PC公司都涉猎了零售，但结果各不相同。

sentences.english: Various styles ask for different designs.
sentences.chinese: 不同文体的板书设计各不相同。

sentences.english: The colours vary from yellow to red.
sentences.chinese: 颜色从黄到红各不相同。

sentences.english: The goals of yoga are varied and range from improving health to achieving Moksha (enlightenment).
sentences.chinese: 瑜珈的目的各不相同，从强身健体到寻求开悟。

sentences.english: All generalists are not created equal.
sentences.chinese: 所有多面手水平各不相同。

sentences.english: Nativized Englishes are shown at various levels of the English language and distinct from each other.
sentences.chinese: 本土化英语表现在语言的各个层面，而且各不相同。

sentences.english: Most studies were cross-sectional and sample sizes varied.
sentences.chinese: 大多数研究是代表性研究并且样本大小各不相同。

sentences.english: A declared guilt differs greatly from typical guilts.
sentences.chinese: 法定一罪与典型数罪各不相同。

sentences.english: On the different levels of forest aesthetics, the concepts of trueness are different.
sentences.chinese: 在森林审美的不同层次中，“真”的表达各不相同。

sentences.english: Cherries vary in colour from almost black to yellow.
sentences.chinese: 樱桃的颜色由近乎黑到黄各不相同。

sentences.english: There are no words or language; their voice makes no sound.
sentences.chinese: 把一次呼气切换成各不相同的声音就形成了语言。

sentences.english: Within an infected area, the intensity of the disease can vary from one village to the next.
sentences.chinese: 在受感染地区内，各村的疾病严重程度可各不相同。

sentences.english: Oak trees a few feet apart differ in the size and shape of their acorns.
sentences.chinese: 几英尺高的橡树在橡树果形状和大小上都各不相同。

sentences.english: Regarding the actual out-of-pocket cost, this varies from situation to situation.
sentences.chinese: 至于实际出实付成本，这情况各不相同的情况。

definition: virtually the same/differing only on small points
as different as can be (idiom)/poles apart
not at all the same/substantially different
entirely different/different as black and white
by no means an isolated case/numerous
